org.knime.core.node.streamable

Class StreamableOperator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.node.streamable.StreamableOperator
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    LagColumnStreamableOperator, StreamableFunction

    public abstract class StreamableOperator
extends Object
    Performs the execution of a node in streamed/distributed mode. Objects are created in a node model. There is only one instance of an operator if the node model requires all inputs to be non-distributable. There are several instances of a streamable operator if the input is distributed, whereby these instances are possibly created in different JVMs (when run in a compute cluster/cloud).
    Since:
    2.6
    Author:
    Bernd Wiswedel, KNIME.com, Zurich, Switzerland
    See Also:
    NodeModel.createStreamableOperator(PartitionInfo, org.knime.core.node.port.PortObjectSpec[])
    No public API: not to be extended by clients
    Pending API.
    No public API: not to be implemented by clients
    Pending API.

      • runFinal

        public abstract void runFinal(PortInput[] inputs,
                              PortOutput[] outputs,
                              ExecutionContext exec)
                       throws Exception
        Performs the execution on the input and (possibly) produces the output. The array elements of the inputs argument must be cast to specific classes. The class depends on the InputPortRole of the corresponding port (as described by NodeModel.getInputPortRoles(). If it is streamable (which can only be true for data ports), then the object can be cast to RowInput. If it's non streamable, then it's an instance of PortObjectInput.

        The outputs argument contains non-null output handles in either of the two cases: (i) all of the inputs are non-distributable (only one instance of a streamable operator that generates the final output) or (ii) the corresponding output is distributable (NodeModel.getOutputPortRoles(). Non-null output handles need to be filled by this method.

        Parameters:
        inputs - The input handles.
        outputs - The output handles (may contain null, see above).
        exec - The context for cancelation, progress reporting.
        Throws:
        Exception - Any exception to indicate an error, cancelation.

      • runIntermediate

        public void runIntermediate(PortInput[] inputs,
                            ExecutionContext exec)
                     throws Exception
        Called when the corresponding NodeModel.iterate(StreamableOperatorInternals) returns true. It performs one iteration on the input data to, e.g. adjust clusters or compute data statistics. The result of this run will be persisted in saveInternals() and fed back to NodeModel.iterate(StreamableOperatorInternals) (after aggregated using a MergeOperator.

        The default implementation is empty.

        Parameters:
        inputs - The input handles.
        exec - The execution context (progress/cancelation)
        Throws:
        Exception - Any exception to abort the calculation.

      • loadInternals

        public void loadInternals(StreamableOperatorInternals internals)
        Called to restore intermediate results when used in an iterative manner. The argument internals contain information aggregated by the MergeOperator.mergeIntermediate(StreamableOperatorInternals[]) method.
        Parameters:
        internals - To restore from.

      • saveInternals

        public StreamableOperatorInternals saveInternals()
        Create the internals calculated during execution that need to be merged and fed back to the node that controls the execution. Only distributed streamable operator should have internals (and only if they need to pass information to the node, e.g. parts of the output object or view internals or warning messages).
        Returns:
        The internals that are transferred back to the client. Internals of different operators are merged using a MergeOperator.
